ork; Integration fits. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: Not AI-related. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because behavior text is about local import/hook ordering only.","test_description":"Candidate (Integration): Entry module sets a global/marker during import; onLoad asserts marker exists and records success. Run loader and assert no assertion failure plus expected record. Catches regressions calling onLoad before import side effects run. Adjacent alternative (Unit): Test a helper that sequences calls [import, onLoad] in mocked order. Catches trivial sequencing logic but can miss real async import/execution ordering bugs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its onLoad hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Failure appears in interaction among dependency graph filtering, error handling, and continuation policy across multiple plugins. REAL-INFRA: In-process execution with local fixtures is enough; no OS/network/subprocess requirement, so not System. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: Deterministic non-LLM orchestration; not Agentic/Workflow. REJECTION-GATE: Higher levels are disqualified by behavior text limiting scope to loader continuation after hook exception.","test_description":"Candidate (Integration): Create plugins: F throws in onLoad, D depends on F, and I independent. Run loader. Assert I onLoad executed, D not executed, and F error recorded. Catches real failure where loader aborts all plugins or ignores dependency impact. Adjacent alternative (Unit): Test error-handler function returns \"continue\" for independent plugins. Catches policy logic bugs but misses wiring bug where executor still halts globally.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"